# Isaac Lab — overlay configuration
#
# Isaac Lab (https://isaac-sim.github.io/IsaacLab/) is a Python framework for
# robot learning that runs ON TOP of Isaac Sim. It is not a standalone image —
# it uses Isaac Sim as its physics and rendering backend.
#
# Always pin Isaac Lab to a tag/commit that supports the Isaac Sim image you use.
# Do not clone an unpinned main branch for thesis work.
#
# Source this file ON TOP of a version config:
#   source configs/isaac-sim-5.1.0.env
#   source configs/isaac-lab.env
#   ./isaac_vmctl.sh start isaacsim --headless
#
# ─── Integration Patterns ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PATTERN A — Keep Isaac Lab in your fork or project workspace:
#   1. Clone/pin IsaacLab under this repo, for example:
#        external/IsaacLab
#   2. Record the exact IsaacLab tag/commit in your project README.
#   3. Run commands through the mounted workspace:
#        ./isaac_vmctl.sh run -- bash -lc 'cd external/IsaacLab && ./isaaclab.sh --install'
#   4. For a remote UI on SimplePod, launch the Isaac Lab script itself with
#      WebRTC livestreaming instead of starting a separate Isaac Sim session:
#        ./isaac_vmctl.sh run --livestream public -- \
#          bash -lc 'cd external/IsaacLab && ./isaaclab.sh -p scripts/tutorials/00_sim/launch_app.py'
#
#      If the task renders camera sensors, add:
#        ./isaac_vmctl.sh run --livestream public --enable-cameras -- \
#          bash -lc 'cd external/IsaacLab && ./isaaclab.sh -p scripts/demos/quadrupeds.py'
#
#      If automatic public-IP detection is wrong, add:
#        --public-ip <reachable-ip>
#
#   The repo is mounted at /workspace/isaac-projects inside the container.
#   Container-local files outside that mount are disposable.
#
# PATTERN B — Custom Docker image (reproducible, recommended for lab projects):
#   Build an image that inherits FROM nvcr.io/nvidia/isaac-sim:<version> and
#   pre-installs a pinned IsaacLab tag/commit:
#
#     docker build -f containers/isaac-lab.Dockerfile \
#       --build-arg ISAAC_IMAGE=nvcr.io/nvidia/isaac-sim:5.1.0 \
#       --build-arg ISAAC_LAB_REF=<tag-or-commit> \
#       -t rice/isaac-lab:<tag> .
#
#   Then set ISAAC_IMAGE to your built image tag below.
#
# ─── Variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Override with your Isaac Lab-extended image if using Pattern B:
# export ISAAC_IMAGE=your-registry/isaac-lab:5.1.0

# Enable the ROS 2 bridge extension — required for ROS 2 <-> Isaac Lab topics.
export ISAAC_EXTRA_ARGS="--/app/enableExtensions/0=omni.isaac.ros2_bridge"

# Isaac Lab extension loading takes more time than bare Isaac Sim.
export START_TIMEOUT_SEC=90
